==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: lizard fish
<hw>lizard fish</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any of several mostly tropical marine scopeloid
fish of the family <fam>Synodontidae</fam> having large mouths in
lizardlike heads, especially the <stype>inshore lizardfish</stype>
(<spn>Synodus foetens</spn> syn. <spn>Synodus poeyi</spn>) of Mideastern
and Southern United States and West Indies; -- sometimes called
<altname>sand pike</altname>.</def> <note>A freshwater perch, the
sauger, a different fish, is also called the <it>sand
pike</it>.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> snakefish.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lizard's tail</ent>⟦br⟧
